7 An Act relating to the Health Care Workforce Training
Commission; providing purpose and intent; creating
8 the Rural Health Transformation Workforce
Implementation Revolving Fund; providing for the
9 appropriation, budgeting, and expenditure of funds;
providing for the issuance of warrants; stating
10 purpose of funds; providing restrictions on funds;
providing for promulgation of rules; providing for
11 codification; and declaring an emergency.
12
13
14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
15 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
16 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 697.18.1 of Title 70, unless
17 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
18 In furtherance of its mission to increase access to health care
19 workers in the rural and underserved areas of Oklahoma, the Health
20 Care Workforce Training Commission shall be authorized to receive
21 appropriations from the State Legislature; accept federal funds and
22 grants, and use the same in accordance with federal requirements;
23 and receive and accept donations, grants, contributions, and gifts
24 from any public or private source.
ENGR. H. B. NO. 3066 Page 1

1 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
2 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 697.18.2 of Title 70, unless
3 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
4 A. There is hereby created in the State Treasury a revolving
5 fund for the Health Care Workforce Training Commission to be
6 designated the "Rural Health Transformation Workforce Implementation
7 Revolving Fund". The fund shall be a continuing fund, not subject
8 to fiscal year limitations, and shall consist of all available
9 monies:
10 1. Received by the state as Rural Health Transformation Program
11 Funds pursuant to, but not limited to, the One Big Beautiful Bill
12 Act of 2025, Section 71401 of P.L. 119-21;
13 2. Directed to the state by the federal government for the
14 purposes of recruiting and retaining clinical workforce talent to
15 rural areas, with commitments to serve rural communities for a
16 minimum of five (5) years, or any other lawful purpose established
17 by the One Big Beautiful Bill Act of 2025;
18 3. Derived as interest and income from deposits and investments
19 of fund assets; and
20 4. Designated for deposit by law.
21 B. 1. All monies accruing to the credit of said fund are
22 hereby appropriated and may be budgeted and expended by the Health
23 Care Workforce Training Commission for authorized purposes as
24 provided in paragraph 2 of this subsection. Expenditures from said
ENGR. H. B. NO. 3066 Page 2

1 fund shall be made upon warrants issued by the State Treasurer
2 against claims filed as prescribed by law with the Director of the
3 Office of Management and Enterprise Services for approval and
4 payment.
5 2. All monies accruing to the credit of said fund shall be
6 utilized for the purpose of recruiting and retaining clinical
7 workforce talent to the rural and underserved areas of Oklahoma or
8 any other lawful purpose established by the One Big Beautiful Bill
9 Act of 2025, including the costs and expenses of operating such
10 programs.
11 3. All monies accruing to the credit of said fund shall be
12 budgeted, expended, and transferred in strict accordance with
13 applicable state and federal laws and guidance that provides
14 limitations on the utilization of such funds.
15 C. The Health Care Workforce Training Commission shall be
16 authorized to promulgate any additional rules necessary for
17 implementation of the Rural Health Transformation Program.
18 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
19 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
20 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
21 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
